The paper deals with distributed computing algorithms for a specific model called Congested Cliques, which is a well-studied topic in the area of distributed computing (cs.DC). The focus of the paper is on symmetry-breaking problems, which is a subfield of distributed algorithms (cs.DS). The paper also involves graph theory and combinatorics, which are relevant to the subcategories cs.GT and cs.NI. Finally, the paper proposes new algorithms and analyzes their running time, which falls under the category of algorithms (cs.AL).
